# **Cheat Sheets Folder (Bandit 1–20)**

### **1. SSH Basics**

```bash
# Connect to Bandit
ssh banditX@bandit.labs.overthewire.org -p 2220

# Using private key
ssh -i private.key banditX@bandit.labs.overthewire.org -p 2220
```

### **2. File Navigation**

```bash
ls        # list files
ls -a     # include hidden files
cd DIR    # change directory
pwd       # print working directory
```

### **3. File Viewing**

```bash
cat file.txt       # show file content
less file.txt      # scrollable view
head file.txt      # first 10 lines
tail file.txt      # last 10 lines
```

### **4. File Searching**

```bash
grep "text" file.txt          # search text in file
grep -r "text" ./             # search recursively
find /path -name "filename"   # find file by name
```

### **5. File Info**

```bash
file file.txt      # check file type
du -h file.txt     # file size
ls -l              # detailed listing with permissions
chmod 600 file     # set private permissions
chmod 700 script   # set executable permissions
```

### **6. Encodings & Transformations**

```bash
# Base64
base64 -d file.b64 > output

# ROT13
tr 'A-Za-z' 'N-ZA-Mn-za-m' < input

# Hexdump to binary
xxd -r file.hex > file

# Command chaining
cat file.txt | grep "text"
```

### **7. Temporary Files**

```bash
mkdir /tmp/tmpname   # create directory
mktemp -d           # create unique temp dir
cp file /tmp/tmpdir  # copy files
mv file newname      # rename files
```

### **8. Port & Network**

```bash
# Scan ports
nmap -p 31000-32000 localhost

# Test SSL service
openssl s_client -connect localhost:PORT

# Netcat
nc localhost PORT
```

### **9. Comparing Files**

```bash
diff file1 file2   # find differences
```

### **10. Setuid / Binary Execution**

```bash
./binary           # run local binary
```

